data.description: Welcome to your new home, pool and lakeview! Back on the market following some work being taken care of to include: Pool pump repaired, and pool treated (beautiful blue now); landscaping fully cleaned up; house power washed; all bathroom sink faucets replaced; home chemically remediated for cigarette smoke smell; professional deep cleaning done.  NEW HVAC installed in 2022. Move-in ready!  When the owner had this house built, it was done to his wishes as a 2-bedroom home in which he enlarged the open dining area and made what would have been a third bedroom into a dedicated home office. The two bedrooms are separated, one to each side of the house and each having private bathrooms. The home sits on the peaceful shores of a quiet and picturesque lake with its own private dock. The inground, heated saltwater pool is surrounded by a nice sized, fenced backyard, all of which can be enjoyed from a screened in patio as well as poolside. The living area boasts an abundance of natural light, raised ceilings that are even vaulted in the kitchen area. The crown molding detail adds that extra touch. The well laid out kitchen is a cook's delight, featuring ample cabinet space, and generous granite counter tops for meal preparation and entertaining. Prepare to be amazed by the secret room located above the garage – this unexpected delight that can be used as a private retreat, craft area or whatever your imagination can come up with. This versatile space offers endless possibilities and is sure to impress. SELLER'S FAVORITE things about the house: The kitchen (because he loves to cook) and the pool. SELLER'S FAVORITE things about the area: It’s a quiet area that is stable. People love living there! Don't miss the opportunity to make this extraordinary property your own. Call today for your private tour!
